  "instructions": [
    "Heat the coconut oil in a large skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for another minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the Thai holy basil and cook until wilted, about 2 minutes.",
    "In a separate bowl, mix together the coconut milk, lemon juice, honey, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the egg to the bowl and whisk until smooth.",
    "Pour the egg mixture over the basil mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture is thick and creamy, about 5 minutes.",
    "Use a spoon to create wells in the mixture and crack an egg into each well.",
    "Season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Top with chopped parsley, mint, and crumbled goat cheese, if using.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional parsley and mint if desired."
  ],
